article.description: Jourdan Stickler scored a career-high 22 points to lead seven Houston Baptist players in double figures as the Huskies cruised to a 109-84 win over Hillsdale Free Will Baptist on Monday night.
article.headline: Houston Baptist beats Hillsdale Free Will Baptist 109-84
article.linkText: Houston Baptist beats Hillsdale Free Will Baptist 109-84
article.story: HOUSTON -- Jourdan Stickler scored a career-high 22 points to lead seven Houston Baptist players in double figures as the Huskies cruised to a 109-84 win over Hillsdale Free Will Baptist on Monday night. Stickler made 8 of 10 field goals attempts, including a career-best six 3-pointers for the Huskies (13-7). Colter Lasher scored 16 and Alex Fountain 14. Caleb Crayton and Isaiah Robinson added 12 points apiece while Reveal Chukwujekwu scored 11 and Trey Patterson had 10 with a career-high eight assists. Houston Baptist has won nine games in a row and 11 of its last 12. A 3-pointer by Trey Snead pulled Hillsdale within two with five minutes left in the first half, but Stickler made a layup and Patterson converted a 3-point play to spark a 14-0 run that spanned halftime and made it 51-35 with 18 minutes to play. The Huskies cruised from there. Adam Morales led Hillsdale -- a member of the National Christian College Athletic Association -- with 21 points.
